	"description": "This article should serve as an all-in-one essential guide for Node.js&#x27; favorite\nsidekick: npm.\n\nNode.js has been taking the world by storm since 2009. Hundreds of thousands of\nsystems have been built using Node.js, prompting the developer community to\nclaim that &quot;JavaScript is eating software&quot;. \n\nOne of the major factors of Node&#x27;s success is npm - its popular package manager,\nwhich allows JavaScript developers to share useful packages like lodash\n[https://www.npmjs.com/package/lodash] and momen",
